title: Keynote: Responsible AI and Community
description: A welcome keynote introducing the event's theme on Responsible AI and its influence on the local developer community. Ankit and Principal Sir will set the tone for the day, outlining the agenda and vision for the future of AI in Prayagraj.

title: Session 1: Utilize the Power of AI with Flutter App Development
description: In this session, Dhrumil will explore the integration of AI into Flutter applications, demonstrating how developers can make their mobile apps smarter and more intuitive with AI-powered features.

title: Session 2: Web Capabilities in AI with Baseline and Wasm
description: In this session, Vrijraj will explain Baseline and how the latest web technologies, such as WebAssembly (Wasm) and WebGPU, enable running AI and machine learning workloads directly in the browser for enhanced performance, security, and privacy.

title: Photo Session
description: A group photo session for all attendees, speakers, and organizers to capture the memories of the event.

title: Lunch Break
description: Enjoy a delicious lunch and networking with fellow attendees, speakers, and organizers.

title: Session 3: Trust and Safety
description: In this session, Explore the advanced mechanisms behind trust and safety at Google, keeping the web secure for billions of users every day.

title: Session 4: AI and Generative AI in Web Development
description: In this session, we'll dive deep into AI and Generative AI and its potential impact on web development, highlighting real-world use cases and future trends in AI-powered web applications.

title: Session 3: Serverless AI with Cloud Run GPU
description: In this session, Anubhav will cover how to deploy AI models in a serverless environment using Google Cloud Run with GPU, illustrating the benefits of scaling AI workloads with serverless technologies.

title: Session 4: Multimodal Search & Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAGs) Powered by Google Search
description: In this session, Yogesh will showcase the potential of Multimodal Search and RAGs (Retrieval-Augmented Generation), explaining how they can be integrated with Google Search for enhanced information retrieval and responsible AI practices.

title: Closing Remarks and Networking
description: Final thoughts and appreciation for all speakers and attendees. An excellent opportunity for developers to network with industry experts and fellow attendees for future collaborations.
